    "body": "There is currently no sane way to represent `enum class` in `.pxd`.\r\n\r\n``` cpp\r\nnamespace lol {\r\nenum class rofl : int {\r\n    SOMETHING,\r\n    MOAR = 1337\r\n};\r\n\r\n// at this point, accessible as rofl::MOAR\r\n}\r\n// here, accessible as lol::rofl::MOAR\r\n```\r\n\r\nA possible way of representing it would be:\r\n\r\n``` cython\r\ncdef extern from \"headername.h\" namespace \"lol\":\r\n    cdef enumclass rofl:\r\n        SOMETHING\r\n        MOAR\r\n\r\n# accessed as\r\nrofl.MOAR\r\n```\r\n\r\nRelated:  #1567",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "The best workaround for this issue that I found with current Cython:\r\n\r\n``` cython\r\ncdef extern from \"headername.h\" namespace \"lol\":\r\n    cdef cppclass rofl:\r\n        pass\r\n        \r\n    cdef rofl rofl_SOMETHING \"rofl::SOMETHING\"\r\n    cdef rofl rofl_MOAR \"rofl::MOAR\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis can be used in the `pyx` file like this:\r\n\r\n``` cython\r\ncdef void f(rofl arg):\r\n    pass\r\n\r\nf(rofl_SOMETHING)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich will generate the correct C++ code.",
            "created_at": "2017-02-12T00:59:47Z",
